              <flipboard active-id='14' nav-type='caption' show-nav-arrows='true'>
                <story-points>
                  <story-point caption='This project explores cancellation behavior and ADR feature across Avalon Hotels using interactive dashboards designed for executive decision-making and operational insight.' captured-sheet='Dashboard: Cancellation Overview' id='1' />
                  <story-point caption='Cancellation risk increases during peak booking periods and varies significantly by customer segment, lead time, and traveler behavior.' captured-sheet='Booking Demand and Cancellation Trend' id='2' />
                  <story-point caption='High-volume booking channels also represent the greatest cancellation exposure, highlighting the importance of segment-specific forecasting and analysis.' captured-sheet='Segment Cancellation Flow' id='3' />
                  <story-point caption='Behavioral and reservation patterns strongly influence cancellation risk across Avalon Hotels. Flexible booking terms, online channels, and longer lead times are associated with higher cancellation exposure, while guest engagement signals such as special requests and repeat bookings indicate greater reservation stability.' captured-sheet='Dashboard: Cancellation Risk Drivers' id='4' />
                  <story-point caption='Online bookings generate the highest volume but also carry the greatest cancellation risk, while Direct and Offline TA/TO channels show stronger reservation stability. The chart helps identify which segments drive reliable revenue versus higher operational risk.' captured-sheet='Cancellation Risk by ADR' id='5'>
