                  </story-point>
                  <story-point caption='Non-refundable bookings consistently experience the highest cancellation activity, particularly for medium-to-long lead times, while refundable and no-deposit bookings show lower overall risk patterns.' captured-sheet='Cancellation Risk by Lead Time &amp; Deposit Type' id='6' />
                  <story-point caption='Cancellation behavior changes noticeably across deposit types and booking lead times. Non-refundable reservations show consistently higher cancellation rates, especially for medium and longer booking windows. Non-refundable bookings consistently experience the highest cancellation activity, particularly for medium-to-long lead times, while refundable and no-deposit bookings show lower overall risk patterns. indicating greater reservation volatility within those segments.' captured-sheet='Cancellation by Length, Lead TIme' id='7'>
                    <capturedDeltas>
                      <worksheet name='Cancellation Risk by Lead Time &amp; Deposit Type'>
                        <selection-collection />
                      </worksheet>
                    </capturedDeltas>
                  </story-point>
                  <story-point caption='Average Daily Rate (ADR) peaks during the summer months and weekends, while customer segments such as Online and Direct bookings show wider pricing variation and higher premium room rates.' captured-sheet='Dashboard: ADR Overview' id='8' />
                  <story-point caption='ADR distribution varies significantly across market segments, with Online and Direct bookings showing the widest pricing ranges and highest premium outliers. This indicates stronger revenue opportunities but also greater pricing variability across those customer groups.' captured-sheet='ADR Distribution by Segment' id='9' />
                  <story-point caption='ADR rates remain relatively stable throughout the week, with slightly higher pricing observed on weekends, reflecting increased leisure travel demand.' captured-sheet='ADR by Weekday' id='10' />
                  <story-point caption='Higher ADR values are associated with Online and Direct bookings, longer stays, and shorter booking lead times, highlighting key revenue-driving reservation patterns.' captured-sheet='Dashboard: ADR Performance Drivers (2)' id='11' />
                  <story-point caption='Online bookings generate the highest booking volume while maintaining above-average ADR, making them the strongest revenue-driving segment, while Direct bookings represent a smaller but premium-priced customer group.' captured-sheet='ADR by Booking Volume' id='12'>
